scene.message:
Masked Boy: She should be{nl}
painting on the floor below.{waitkey}{clearbox}Sealing the "Gate of{nl}
Paradise" shut with the{nl}
black of despair.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Her...{waitkey}{nl}
The girl in the white mask{nl}
from the art room?{waitkey}{ret}

Masked Boy: I see.{waitkey}{nl}
That's just like her.{waitkey}{clearbox}This frozen school is, after{nl}
all, just a byproduct{nl}
of her heart.{waitkey}Whichever way it turns, it{nl}
has no bearing on my plan.{waitkey}{ret}

Masked Boy: I too have long{nl}
thought schools unnecessary.{waitkey}{clearbox}Education need only be given{nl}
to the chosen few.{waitkey}{clearbox}If she desires destruction,{nl}
it may be wise to humor her.{waitkey}{ret}

Masked Boy: Now then.{waitkey}{nl}
Think it over hard with{nl}
that dull head of yours.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: The higher we climb,{nl}
the colder it gets~{waitkey}{clearbox}How many floors are left...{nl}
sigh...{waitkey}{ret}
